Cig’arrête is an android application still in development. This application allows the user to monitor his cigarette consumption, check some advice, depending on his dependence, to reduce his cigarette consumption, check how much he economized and what he can buy thanks that (athletics, hardware and edible rewards). The user can also create his own goals and how much money he has to economize. The source codes are available in my GitHub. Digikup is a make-up simulation. This desktop application allows to create a mask on eyebrows, lips and cheeks and apply to them some make-up on the picture, set the opacity of the make-up, etc. This application was developed with 5 other IT students and this project was offered by the BU-CROCCS labs, placed at Bangkok, in Thailand.
